cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with deep convolutional neural networks for computer vision tasks, specifically landmark recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel architecture for efficient network learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a reward function for inference path selection also involves reinforcement learning (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the application of the proposed architecture in portable mobile devices, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with landmark recognition based on geographic information, which can be considered as an information retrieval task (cs.IR).
